The rule has nothing to do with the service excellence of teachers in secondary and higher secondary schools. The rule requires that the service excellence of a teacher in primary schools be recognised from the date on which he / she acquires the educational and professional qualifications prescribed for the post. This means that if at the time of appointment, the teacher concerned has held the required qualification, his / her seniority will have to be fixed on the date of joining the service. Such Seda cannot be considered for service excellence if the primary teacher holds a qualification higher than the prescribed requirement. Such a qualification should only be considered an additional qualification. Primary school teachers will be eligible for promotion to the post of "Principal, Primary School * if the post of Principal is sanctioned in that primary school on the basis of such service excellence."

(f) Reference No. Explanation as to whether or not the notification dated 24.03.2023 herein shall continue to have retrospective effect: -

(1) The change made in Category "C" vide Notification D 24.03.2023 at Annexure No.1, includes post-graduates in various disciplines and pedagogy in this category. In fact, such secondary teachers are included in Category "C" when they are graduates. Thus, a master's degree is only an additional qualification.
Similarly, if they are newly appointed, their superannuation will be counted as on the date of their inclusion in Category "C."

(ii) Although the qualification for admission to Category C is a two-year-old course of D.Ed., a primary teacher cannot be appointed to a secondary school on the basis of this qualification and will not actually be admitted to Category C unless appointed as a secondary teacher. Therefore, the inclusion of this qualification has no effect on the service excellence of secondary teachers who are already employed.

(iii) In very exceptional circumstances, there may be a teacher who holds a D.Ed. qualification and has been appointed as a secondary teacher long ago. In such a case, the notification dated 24.03.2023 will not be retroactive. This is because a teacher newly admitted to Category C cannot be superior to a teacher already employed in that category.
(iv) Footnotes-1-A, 9-B, 1CB 91-D are included only to illustrate the existing provisions. So the question of whether or not they will apply retroactively is lost.

04. Taking into account the above entire explanation, Reference No. The institution management is required to take care of determining the seniority of the faculty in the schools where the Act 1 and the rule 2 apply. Reference No. 9 If seniority has been determined by misinterpreting the provisions of the notification herein and the promotion has been made accordingly, that seniority should be immediately revised and the eligible person should be promoted.

All Divisional Deputy Directors of Education and all Education Officers (Primary / Secondary) shall be responsible for bringing the circular to the notice of all concerned. Under no circumstances should a promotion of seniority be granted if it is inconsistent with the provision mentioned in this circular.
